  "texts": [
    "While they can aid in language translation and cultural exchange, there is also a risk of promoting a homogenized culture, overshadowing regional languages and traditions [44].",
    "Feedback loop with bias in data collectionThe use of training data scraped from the internet without careful curation can create a feedback loop where biases are iteratively reinforced and amplified in subsequent models [23].",
    "While the internet is a vast and diverse source of information, it is not entirely representative of all perspectives in society.",
    "Certain groups or viewpoints may be over-represented or underrepresented online.",
    "This imbalance can lead to skewed data sets, which in turn can lead to LLM models that do not fairly represent all sections of society, reinforcing hegemonic viewpoints [7]."
